Title : 2014 Mutua Madrid Open – Men's Singles
Text : {{TennisEvents|2014|Mutua Madrid Open|
|champ = {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Rafael Nadal]]
|runner = {{flagicon|JPN}} [[Kei Nishikori]]
|score  = 2–6, 6–4, 3–0, ret.
}}

{{main|2014 Mutua Madrid Open}}

The '''2014 Mutua Madrid Open – Men's Singles''' was the main men's event of the [[2014 Mutua Madrid Open]] [[tennis]] tournament played in [[Madrid]], Spain from 3 May through 11 May 2014.

[[Rafael Nadal]] was the defending champion. Nadal became the first player who defended his Madrid title since the tournament inception in 2002 when [[Kei Nishikori]] retired in the final because of back injury. Nishikori was leading Nadal 6–2, 4–2, but Nishikori suffered a back injury in the 7th game, allowing Nadal to take the upper hand before ultimately retiring at 0–3 in the 3rd set.<ref name=ATPWorldTour111>{{cite web|last1=Meiseles|first1=Josh|title=Madrid Final How Was Won|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/News/Tennis/2014/05/19/Madrid-Final-How-Was-Won.aspx|website=ATP World Tour|accessdate=12 May 2015|date=May 11, 2014}}</ref>

